{#
  Design Science Research (DSR) Template
  ======================================
  DSR methodology structure: Problem, Artifact, Evaluation, Theory.
  For creating and evaluating design artifacts.

  Required Variables:
  - title: Paper title
  - author: Author name(s)
  - abstract: Paper abstract

  Optional Variables:
  - problem: Problem identification content
  - artifact: Artifact design content
  - evaluation: Artifact evaluation content
  - theory: Theoretical contribution content
  - date: Publication date (defaults to \today)
  - bibliography: Bibliography file name (defaults to 'references')

  Usage:
    const context = {
      title: "Designing a Semantic CLI Framework",
      author: "Design Scientist",
      abstract: "This DSR paper presents...",
      problem: "Organizations struggle with...",
      artifact: "We designed a framework...",
      evaluation: "Laboratory and field evaluation...",
      theory: "Generalizable design principles..."
    };
#}
